meanings.definition: To outperform in a theatrical performance.
meanings.sent1: The magician outacted his rival with an amazing trick.
meanings.sent2: The dance group outacted all others with their synchronized routine.
meanings.sent3: The clown outacted the audience by slipping on a banana peel.
meanings.sent4: The sun outacted the moon in the celestial performance of the night sky.
meanings.sent5: The acrobat outacted gravity with her breathtaking stunts.
